<br>
<b><a NAME="1394">1394 Showcase</A></b><br>Hosted by the 1394 Trade Association <p>
1394 technology could well be the most dramatic development in the consumer electronics arena.  Providing near universal connectivity and interoperability of digital video and audio among all sorts of devices, IEEE 1394 applications are going to affect anybody and everybody who makes, sells or uses consumer electronics.  Learn all about it at the 1394 Showcase in the South Hall, LVCC.  See how 1394 technology will make it possible to interconnect and control virtually any assortment of digital devices, such as DVD and CD players, digital converter boxes, DTVs, digital surround sound processors/receivers and digital VCR players. This promises to be one of the most heavily visited pavilions at CES, and with good reason. See industry leaders like Texas Instruments, Apple, Sony, Panasonic, Kenwood, and many others.
 <br>
 <br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a name="Antennas">Antenna</A></b><br>See the latest in our digital link to the future!  Direct Broadcast Satellite (DBS) systems and high definition televisions (HDTV) have made antennas a must.  See the newest in sleek, innovative, high-performance indoor and outdoor designs in the CES Antenna Pavilion in the North Hall, LVCC.  Exhibitors include Winegard, Interactive Technology, Terk Technologies and Channel Master.  You also can visit the web site that shows the correct antenna to use in different locations, <a href=http://www.Antennaweb.org>www.AntennaWeb.org</a>, and see how the CEA Antenna Selector Maps are helping retailers choose the right antenna for their customers.<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a name="Digital_Hollywood">Digital Hollywood</A></b><br>
Digital Hollywood in the North Hall, LVCC, is the meeting place for the brightest stars of the entertainment and technology industries, and a showcase for state-of-the-art consumer technology.  Sun, Microsoft, Pinnacle, TiVo Replay Networks, 3Com, and Cisco are already making a buzz with their digital convergence technologies.  See the digital marketplace of the future, with exhibits from the industry leaders, including ClearBand, DigiScents, Webstakes.com and Packet Video.<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
<br>
<b><a NAME="Digital_Imaging">Digital Imaging Pavilion</a></b><br>Sponsored by PhotoHighway.com <p>
See the big picture in the Digital Imaging Pavilion in the North Hall, LVCC.  The digital market continues to explode as pixel counts increase and prices decrease.  The photo industry is promising to make digital imaging easy, fun and affordable for all. Don't miss the digital cameras, flashcards, scanners and OCRs, software, monitors, printers, memory (film), batteries, cases and paper, not to mention video and electronic imaging and manipulation products, switchers, presentation equipment, imaging boards and training media.  You'll see industry leaders such as Aeon, Gamla, Pixera and California Electronics.<br>
<br>

 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
<br>
<b><a NAME="Digital_Radio">Digital Radio Pavilion</A></b><br> 
The future of radio sounds digital - see it at the Digital Radio Pavilion in the Sands Expo and Convention Center, Upper Level.  Digital radio offers consumers interference-free reception, near CD-quality sound, and a wide choice of data services.  The industry leaders will be showcasing this revolutionary technology.  Look for Lucent, Sirius Satellite Radio, XM Radio, Digital Radio Express, and USA Digital Radio in the mobile electronics area of the Sands!<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a NAME="DSL">DSL Showcase</A></b><br> Hosted by ADSL Forum<p> 
Digital Subscriber Line (DSL) is a modem technology that transforms ordinary phone lines (also known as "twisted copper pairs") into high-speed digital lines for ultra-fast Internet access. DSL also enables access to corporate networks for telecommuters, as well as exciting new interactive multimedia applications such as multiplayer gaming, video on demand and video catalogs.  DSL is the Internet's future; see it today at the DSL Showcase in the North Hall, LVCC.<br>

 
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="E-Commerce">E-Commerce Pavilion</A></b><br>Sponsored by <i></i>PC Computing</i> and <i>Yahoo! Internet Life</i><p>
Electronic commerce is multiplying.  More consumers are buying more products online than ever before.  See how you can sell more, streamline business operations, or automate customer service at the E-Commerce Pavilion, located in the North Hall. Pivotal players who make electronic commerce happen will be exhibiting:  Knowledgelink, Xpedior, CETRADE.COM, CDS Solutions, Information Management Consultants, Audiocafe.com, Roxy.com and Assist Cornerstone Technology
<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a NAME="Emerging_Technologies">Emerging Technologies</A></b><br> 
See tomorrow's technologies today at the Emerging Technologies Pavilion in the North Hall, LVCC.  This showcase benefits everyone involved in consumer technologies.  Financiers, investors, venture capitalists, retail buyers, the press and media, engineers and industry analysts flock here to see more than 30 growth companies and their next-generation technologies.  The Emerging Technologies Pavilion is the most-visited pavilion at CES!<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a NAME="Home_Security">Home Security</A></b><br>
Home automation and security are among the fastest growing product categories at CES.  Stop by the North Hall, LVCC to learn about the latest in integrated security systems, identification products, access control systems, intrusion detection devices, perimeter protection systems, and CCTV.  See exhibitors such as:  OK Security, Digital Security Controls, Clover, ITI, Wooju America, Seaview, and Artek USA Orchid, and Windmaster.<br>
<br>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="IDB">Intelligent Data Bus (IDB)</A></b><br>
Sponsored by IDB Forum<p> 
Intelligent Data Bus (IDB) plug-and-play technology enables consumers to buy and go.  Go to the IDB Pavilion, in the Sands Expo and Convention Center, Upper Level, to see the hottest aftermarket car products at CES.<BR><BR>

 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="ITS">Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS)</A></b><br>
Endorsed by ITS America<p> 
Experience products that improve both passenger and freight efficiency as well as safety along surface transportation modes.  The ITS Pavilion focuses on vehicle navigation, global positioning systems, geographic information systems (GIS) satellites, vehicle safety, obstacle warning systems, emergency notification and wireless products.  Meet the partners you'll need to tap into the ITS marketplace on the upper level of the Sands Expo and Convention Center.  Exhibitors include: Navigation Technologies, Etak, TravRoute, ETL, InfoMove.com, and RoyalTek.<BR><BR>

 

 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="IRDA">IrDA (Infrared Data Association)</A></b><br>
Infrared is showing up in several consumer technologies, such as PDAs, printers, desktop adapters, notebooks, cameras, and palm devices. Infrared will soon be seen in copiers, fax machines, overhead projectors, telephones, bank ATM's, credit cards, game controls, and headsets.  Catch the latest and greatest at the IrDa Pavilion in the North Hall, LVCC.<BR><BR>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="MP3">MP3 @ <i>Upside's </i> Digital Living Room </A></b><br>
MP3 is an audio compression format that speeds up the transfer of digital music files.  MP3 compresses music by deleting certain audio signals from a digital recording, thus making it feasible to download music over the Internet.  Most forecasters expect to see quick growth for MP3 in the next few years and a brilliant future for portable audio devices and Internet audio. Catch the crest of the next Internet wave at MP3 at the Digital Living Room Pavilion, North Hall, LVCC.  Partial exhibitor list includes:  Hyun Won, Request Multimedia, Digital Voice Systems, Lydstrom, Casady & Greene, I-Jam Multimedia, MaxTech, Ziplabs and Dream Quest.<BR><BR>
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<b><a NAME="Speech_Technology">Speech Technology</A></b><br>Sponsored by <i>Speech Technology Magazine</i> 
Speech recognition is a key competitive technology in the consumer marketplace.  If you want to see the latest and best voice-activated products in the areas of telephony, computers, automotive, consumer electronics, Internet, and more, then come to the Speech Technology Pavilion in the North Hall, LVCC.  Exhibitors include Emkay, Sensory, Sycom, and Telex.  See industry innovations and exciting consumer applications, such as vehicle navigation, home automation, and video games.  Here's your chance to make OEM/licensing partnerships, integrate the latest voice technology applications into your product lines, and expand your distribution channels. 
 <br>
<br>
 
 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="Timepiece">Timepiece Pavilion</A></b><br>
By popular demand, the International CES is introducing the Timepiece Pavilion, located in the North Hall, LVCC.  This pavilion showcases the finest in timepieces and related timepiece products.  Here's your opportunity to see the latest and most exciting timepieces, clocks, and other personal electronics products that keep the world on time.  Visit these cutting-edge exhibitors in the Timepiece Pavilion: Luxury International, Europa Wholesale, Pearl International, Wani's Enterprises, Titanium Marketing, Geneva Timepiece, Favour Light Enterprises, Eastern Watch, M&T Vision, Teltime Watch, Timestar, Tru-Time Watch, About Time, Juno International.<BR><BR>






 <A HREF="#top">Top</A>
 <br>
<B><a NAME="Upsides_Digital_Living_Room">Upside's Digital Living Room</A></b><br>
From digital televisions to voice-controlled thermostats, <i>Upside's</i> Digital Living Room Pavilion shows how to entertain the digital consumer of tomorrow - and simplify his life as well.  Lifestyle and workstyle both get a boost in the Digital Living Room, as consumer electronics intersects with the entertainment, computer, and Internet industries.  See demonstrations and exhibitors that stimulate your mind on the digital opportunities for the home market in the North Hall, LVCC.  Partial exhibitor list:  Integra, Telecruz, Siemens, Intrigo, Hy-Tek, Avio, Electronic Home Networks, Neurosmith, 2wire, Replay, KBA, HomePNA, Ravisent, Netpliance, Liquid Audio, Echogent, RF Link, Apogee.<BR><BR>
